Adia Nutrition plans to move from OTC Pink Sheets to OTCQB Venture Market through a third-party audit.
news.summary: Winter Park, Florida, on February 5, 2025 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) - Adia Nutrition Inc. (OTC Pink: ADIA), a company known for its innovative nutritional products and medical treatments, recently disclosed its decision to engage a PCAOB (Public Company Accounting Oversight Board) accounting firm to carry out a thorough third-party audit. This decision stems from a collaborative effort with Adia’s accountant and is a strategic step in their objective to transition their shares from the OTC Pink Sheets to the OTCQB Venture Market. By doing so, Adia aims to increase visibility, broaden its investor base, and showcase its dedication to transparency and expansion.

Global fiber optic components market set to reach $58.65 billion by 2030, growing at 9.8% CAGR. Market worth $36.69 billion in 2025.
news.summary: In Delray Beach, Florida, it is projected that the worldwide fiber optic components industry will experience significant growth, increasing from a value of $36.69 billion in 2025 to $58.65 billion by the year 2030. This growth represents a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 9.8% during the period from 2025 to 2030 as per a recent report by MarketsandMarkets™. This rise in market value is attributed to factors such as the expanding number of internet users and the demand for high-speed data transmission.

news.headline: Tennessee SHIELD Pilot Program enhances public safety and fiscal responsibility, launching Feb. 5, 2025.

This innovative program aims to boost public safety and use state resources efficiently. The initiative includes cutting-edge safety protocols and aims to revolutionize the way safety is ensured.

Disposable medical supplies market projected to grow by USD 604.17 billion (17.3% CAGR) from 2024-2028, driven by rising demand.

Estimated to increase by USD 604.17 billion between 2024 and 2028, this market is expected to experience a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 17.3% throughout the forecast period.

news.headline: Grant Thornton survey finds CFO optimism surging post-election, with over 250 financial leaders showing confidence in the economy.
news.summary: In Chicago, a recent survey conducted by Grant Thornton, a prominent provider of audit, assurance, tax, and advisory services, unveiled a significant upturn in confidence among chief financial officers (CFOs). The survey, which focused on CFO sentiment for the fourth quarter of 2024, included insights from over 250 senior finance executives. Interestingly, the results showcased a notable shift from the election-related uncertainties of November to a surge in optimism regarding the U.S. economy and achieving business objectives.

news.headline: Lexia Aspire Professional Learning by Cambium earns IDA Accreditation, ensuring quality in educator preparation programs.
news.summary: Lexia Aspire Professional Learning, a professional learning solution by Lexia, a Cambium Learning Group brand in Boston, has received the International Dyslexia Association (IDA) Accreditation Seal. This accreditation is granted through the IDA's Program Review and Accreditation initiative, which focuses on evaluating and improving educator preparation programs (EPPs) systematically. This recognition highlights Lexia's commitment to quality education, with programs accredited based on their effectiveness in supporting learners.

news.headline: More Americans are washing hands during flu season, but 77% noticed others skipping in public restrooms.
news.summary: In Menomonee Falls, Wisconsin, on February 5, 2025, it was reported that although a significant portion of Americans are prioritizing handwashing during the cold and flu season, nearly 80% of individuals have observed others leaving public restrooms without washing their hands.

Situated on the 18th floor of a commercial office building, this project aims to enhance the tenant experience. The endeavor is expected to cost in the millions and is anticipated to be completed by the end of the year, offering various facilities and services to the tenants, such as a lounge area, fitness center, and outdoor terrace.

The company showcased a TV commercial during Sunday's Big Game as part of their strategy. The Boston Beer Company aims to surpass competitors in this market segment and secure the top spot with this new product.

news.headline: Comcast and Dolby partner to stream Super Bowl in Dolby Vision and Dolby Atmos on Xfinity X1 and Stream app.
news.summary: In a groundbreaking collaboration, Comcast and Dolby have joined forces to bring the very first Super Bowl broadcast in Dolby Vision and Dolby Atmos to viewers. This historic event will be available on Xfinity X1 and the Xfinity Stream App, offering an immersive and visually impressive experience to an unprecedented number of fans. news.headline: FM, a custom software builder with AI, targets business owners with generative solutions. Forbes notes focus on trends like hyper personalization and tech integration.

They aim to provide businesses with generative software solutions that allow for fast idea testing, quick iterations, and systematic launches. This approach is said to usher in a new era of opportunities as per the Forbes Business Council. Today's business owners are adapting growth strategies centered around trends like hyper-personalization, integrated technology stacks, and enhanced customer experience. FM's innovative software solutions aim to cater to these evolving needs in the business landscape.

The suite includes AI Front Desk, AI Concierge, AI Central Reservations, and Canary's AI Booking Agent, aiming to enhance the overall guest experience. news.headline: SEC enforcement lawyer Marc Berger joins Latham firm in NY. Leader in SEC from 2017 to 2021. Offers experience in white-collar defense.

With his extensive background, Berger now joins the firm's top-performing White Collar Defense & Investigations Practice, bringing valuable expertise to the team.

Operation Homefront is a non-profit organization that provides emergency assistance and morale to military families, offering a range of programs designed to support them. This partnership aims to contribute to the well-being of military families through various initiatives. Hilton Grand Vacations will be working closely with Operation Homefront to provide a host of resources and support for these families. The partnership between the two organizations is expected to benefit a significant number of military families across the country.

news.headline: Astrolab's FLIP rover to be delivered by Astrobotic's Griffin lander to the Moon's south pole. NASA's CLPS initiative involved.
news.summary: Venturi Astrolab and Astrobotic have revealed that Astrobotic’s Griffin lander will transport Astrolab's rover to the Moon in the Griffin-1 mission. The rover, named FLIP (FLEX Lunar Innovation Platform), will be placed at the Nobile Region of the lunar south pole. Initially intended to carry the VIPER payload for NASA’s Commercial Lunar Payload Services initiative, the Astrobotic mission will now include this new collaboration. This announcement marks a significant step in lunar exploration, with precise details on timing and mission specifics to follow.

news.headline: Vatica Health wins 2025 Best in KLAS Award for Risk Adjustment Software and Professional Services, 3rd year in a row.
news.summary: Vatica Health based in Atlanta has been recognized as the top provider-centric risk adjustment and clinical quality solutions company, securing the Best in KLAS distinction for 2025 in the Risk Adjustment Software and Professional Services sector. This marks the third consecutive year that Vatica has achieved this prestigious recognition. The assessment conducted by KLAS involved extensive research on various vendors in the risk adjustment field, with feedback gathered from numerous health plans and providers through in-depth interviews. Customers evaluated each solution based on six key categories.

The event will provide an opportunity for the company to engage with industry leaders and investors. news.headline: athenahealth wins 3 Best in KLAS awards, incl. Overall Independent Physician Practice Suite, for 2025.

These accolades include Overall Independent Physician Practice Suite - athenahealth, Ambulatory EHR 11-75 Physicians, Independent - athenaClinicals®, and Practice Management 11-75 Physicians, Independent - athenaCollector®. This marks a significant achievement for the company, continuing their streak of recognition from KLAS for the past 19 years, thanks to the invaluable feedback and support from their clientele.

news.headline: North Carolina expected to lead in franchise business growth in 2025, adding 1,397 new franchises, 14,636 jobs, contributing $35.5 billion to state economy.
news.summary: A recent study projects that in 2025, North Carolina is expected to witness the establishment of 1,397 new local franchise businesses, leading to the creation of 14,636 job opportunities. The franchise sector's impact on the state's economy is estimated to reach $35.5 billion in the same year. This growth in franchises will not only provide avenues for business ownership but also drive economic expansion and foster job growth in North Carolina. The study's findings were announced in Washington on February 5, 2025.

news.headline: Metronet to bring 100% fiber-optic internet to Elwood, Indiana with speeds up to 5 gigabits/sec for residents, 10 gigabits/sec for businesses.
news.summary: A company named Metronet, recognized as the "Fastest Major ISP in the Country" by PCMag for two consecutive years, has disclosed its intention to introduce 100% fiber-optic internet in Elwood, Indiana. The initiative involves a substantial private investment in the multimillion-dollar range. This upgraded network will provide high-speed connectivity to numerous residences and commercial establishments. Residents can expect speeds reaching up to five gigabits per second, while businesses will have access to speeds of up to ten gigabits per second. This development aims to enhance the digital infrastructure in the area.
